article.headline: Northern Arizona 84, Montana State 61
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Kelly Golob scored 21 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as Northern Arizona broke open a close game with an early second-half run to beat Montana State 84-61 Thursday night. Ahead 46-43, the Lumberjacks went on a 17-0 run started by Kyle Feuerbach's 3-pointer with 12:07 left in the game. Golob scored eight points during the decisive spurt for Northern Arizona (11-14, 4-8 Big Sky). Feuerbach finished with 14 points and Steve Sir added 11 for the Lumberjacks, who hit 11 of 26 3-pointers. Marvin Moss paced Montana State (13-11, 8-3) with 12 points but only two came after halftime. Ja'Ron Jefferson and Branden Miller added 11 points each for the Bobcats, who hurt themselves with 19 turnovers.
